                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.77/251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-09T13:00:00-05:45"
                            >November 9, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>268. By Presidential decree dated November 8, Mr. Kennedy is appointed acting
                    manager of the Pacific Railway “with the obligation to deposit in the National
                    Bank to the order of the government all funds of the railway,” and Señor Porto
                    Carrero is appointed assistant manager.</p>
                <p>President Moncada has informed me that he has taken this action to insure
                    continuity in the local management and that it does not alter his hope expressed
                    in my telegram 258, October 29, 3 p.m. Kennedy is requesting cable instructions
                    of the White Management Corporation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
